{"lemma":"دَنَفُ","slug":"دَنَفُ","root":"د.ن.ف","root_slug":"د-ن-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ن-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13203","n13205","n13206"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13203","headword_ar":"دَنِفَ","root":"dnf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danafN","text_ar":"دَنَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Adnf","text_ar":"ادنف","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, Mgh, Msb, K;) or, accord. to Sb, one does not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danifa","text_ar":"دَنِفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", though they sometimes said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danifN","text_ar":"دَنِفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for he regarded this as a possessive epithet; (M;) said of a sick man, (S, Mgh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had a constant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chronic, disease:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb: [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danafN","text_ar":"دَنَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below:]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, heavy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of disease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and near to death,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the point of death:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became emaciated by disease so as to be at the point of death."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b2-  And [hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danifati Al$~amosu","text_ar":"دَنِفَتِ الشَّمْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Adnft","text_ar":"ادنفت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sun was near to setting, and became yellow."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danifa AlA^amoru","text_ar":"دَنِفَ الاَمْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"event, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, near"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to passing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Mgh","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n13205","headword_ar":"دَنَفٌ","root":"dnf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A constant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chronic, disease;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as infects,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pervades, the person"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the inside:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any disease, whatever it be."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)       -A2-  Also, (S, M, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danifN","text_ar":"دَنِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) the latter held by Sb to be a possessive epithet, as he disallowed the verb"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danifa","text_ar":"دَنِفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a constant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chronic, disease;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as infects,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pervades, his person"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his inside:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having any disease:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emaciated by disease so as to be at the point of death:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mudonafN","text_ar":"مُدْنَفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mudonifN","text_ar":"مُدْنِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same: (M:) or these two signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered heavy by disease"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to be near to death,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the point of death:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see 1]: (S, Mgh, K:) [and Freytag adds ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAnifN","text_ar":"دَانِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", explained as meaning “ interitui obnoxius, ” as from the Ham; in which I only find (p. 624) authority for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danifN","text_ar":"دَنِفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being at the point of death"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destruction:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danafN","text_ar":"دَنَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used alike as masc. (Fr, T, S, M, K) and fem. (S, M, K) and sing. (Fr, T, S, M, K) and dual (S, M) and pl., (Fr, T, S, M, K,) as though it were an inf. n. used as an epithet: (M:) but if you say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danifN","text_ar":"دَنِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", you vary it for the fem. and dual and pl., (T, * S, M, K,) saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN danifapN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ دَنِفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) &c., (S,) i. e., saying also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulaAni danifaAni","text_ar":"رَجُلَانِ دَنِفَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN A^adonaAfN","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ اَدْنَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijaAlN A^adonaAfN","text_ar":"رِجَالٌ اَدْنَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danafN","text_ar":"دَنَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has a dual form and a pl.; (K;) [i. e.] one may say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axawaAka danafaAni","text_ar":"اَخَوَاكَ دَنَفَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ixowatuka A^adonaAfu","text_ar":"اـِخْوَتُكَ اَدْنَافُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Fr, T.) ―         -b2-  Applied to the sun, it means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Near to setting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"becoming yellow."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA.) So in the saying (of El-'Ajjáj, T, TA),"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waAl$~amosu qado kaAdato takuwnu danafaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the sun had almost become near to setting, and to turning yellow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T, M, TA.) [See Q. 2 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zHlf","text_ar":"زحلف"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","Msb","Mgh","Fr","T","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n13206","headword_ar":"دَنِفٌ","root":"dnf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danafN","text_ar":"دَنَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}